# Koto — environment variable template
#
# Set these in Vercel Dashboard → Project Settings → Environment Variables.
# Never commit real values to this file — only the variable names + a
# one-line comment explaining purpose.
#
# Append-only: new phases add a section at the bottom; never overwrite
# previously-defined keys.

# === Phase 10 — KotoIQ WP plugin thin-shim pivot ===

# Ed25519 private key (PEM, base64-encoded; newline-safe in Vercel env).
# Generate: openssl genpkey -algorithm ed25519 -outform PEM | base64
KOTOIQ_SHIM_DASHBOARD_PRIVKEY=

# Matching Ed25519 public key (PEM, base64-encoded). The shim plugin
# stores its sha256 fingerprint at pairing time and verifies against
# this fingerprint on every signed envelope. Distribute via the
# /api/kotoiq-shim-manifest endpoint (Plan 02).
KOTOIQ_SHIM_DASHBOARD_PUBKEY=

# Per CONTEXT.md D-Keypair-scope: SINGLE GLOBAL KEYPAIR for v1.
# Per-site keypairs deferred to M2.
